open-philip-babymonitor

This project builds on prior reverse-engineering work, all MIT-licensed:

- aventproxy (https://github.com/thekoma/aventproxy)
  Source of the Philips Avent / Tuya Mobile SDK reverse engineering: the
  request signing algorithm, password + email-MFA login flow, MQTT credential
  derivation, and the WebRTC->RTSP bridge. The bridge in `bridge/` is vendored
  from this project (commit 9d1ae98). The Python client in `login/` is a
  reimplementation of its documented API. See bridge/UPSTREAM_LICENSE.

- tuya-ipc-terminal (https://github.com/seydx/tuya-ipc-terminal)
  The bridge that aventproxy forked from.

- go2rtc (https://github.com/AlexxIT/go2rtc)
  WebRTC and codec utilities used by the bridge.

- hls.js (https://github.com/video-dev/hls.js), v1.5.13, Apache-2.0
  Vendored at web/hls.min.js for browser HLS playback.
